High rejection rates in a 12,000-node graph likely stem from similarity window saturation and bridge noise. As density grows, the 0.5 floor captures more superficially similar but intellectually redundant pairs. Check novelty ratio gate failures — if high, raise the floor to 0.55-0.60. Also audit bridge topology: cross-domain pairs from poorly matched domains produce incoherent output. The 2% decay may also be forcing pairing of low-quality nodes. Recommendations: raise similarity floor, audit bridges, add minimum parent weight threshold.